ents%20in%202023.%20We%20are%20afraid%20of%20the%20uncharted%20territory%20that%20we%20have%20now%20entered%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20an%20international%20coalition%20of%20authors%20in%20a%20new%20report%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20BioScience.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETheir%20stark%20assessment%3A%20%26quot%3BLife%20on%20planet%20Earth%20is%20under%20siege%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20said%20humanity%20had%20made%20%26quot%3Bminimal%20progress%26quot%3B%20in%20curbing%20its%20planet-heating%20emissions%2C%20with%20major%20greenhouse%20gases%20at%20record%20levels%2C%20and%20subsidies%20for%20fossil%20fuels%20soaring%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20damning%20assessment%20comes%20just%20a%20month%20ahead%20of%20UN%20COP28%20climate%20negotiations%20to%20be%20held%20in%20the%20oil-rich%20United%20Arab%20Emirates.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20must%20shift%20our%20perspective%20on%20the%20climate%20emergency%20from%20being%20just%20an%20isolated%20environmental%20issue%20to%20a%20systemic%2C%20existential%20threat%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20on%20the%20state%20of%20the%20climate%20looked%20at%20recent%20data%20on%2035%20planetary%20%26quot%3Bvital%20signs%26quot%3B%20and%20found%2020%20of%20these%20were%20at%20record%20extremes%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BOff%20the%20chart%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJust%20roughly%201.2%20degrees%20Celsius%20of%20temperature%20rise%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels%20has%20triggered%20a%20range%20of%20calamitous%20and%20costly%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20year%20has%20also%20seen%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20warming%20El%20Nino%20weather%20phenomenon.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20European%20Union's%20Copernicus%20Climate%20Change%20Service%20has%20said%20that%20the%20three%20months%20to%20September%20were%20the%20hottest%20period%20ever%20recorded%2C%20and%20likely%20the%20hottest%20in%20approximately%20120%2C000%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMany%20climate-related%20records%20were%20broken%20by%20%26quot%3Benormous%20margins%26quot%3B%20in%202023%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20particularly%20temperatures%20in%20the%20oceans%2C%20which%20have%20absorbed%20almost%20all%20the%20excess%20heat%20caused%20by%20human%20carbon%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECo-author%20Johan%20Rockstrom%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Potsdam%20Institute%20for%20Climate%20Impact%20Research%2C%20said%20recorded%20sea%20surface%20temperatures%20%26quot%3Bgo%20completely%20off%20the%20chart%26quot%3B%20and%20scientists%20are%20not%20yet%20able%20to%20fully%20explain%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20potentially%20serious%20impacts%20include%20threats%20to%20sea%20life%20and%20coral%20reefs%20and%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20intensity%20of%20large%20tropical%20storms%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPeople%20across%20the%20planet%20have%20faced%20heatwaves%20and%20droughts%20this%20year%2C%20while%20severe%20flooding%20has%20struck%20in%20the%20US%2C%20China%20and%20India%20and%20beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Canada%2C%20record%20wildfires%20partly%20related%20to%20climate%20change%20released%20more%20carbon%20dioxide%20than%20the%20country's%20total%202021%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.5C%20era%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBefore%202023%2C%20days%20with%20global%20average%20temperatures%20more%20than%201.5C%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels%20were%20a%20rarity%2C%20the%20authors%20said.%20This%20year%20had%20already%20registered%2038%20such%20days%20by%20mid-September.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20ambitious%20Paris%20Agreement%20target%20of%201.5C%20will%20be%20measured%20over%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20lead%20author%20William%20Ripple%2C%20professor%20at%20Oregon%20State%20University%2C%20said%20we%20are%20likely%20entering%20a%20period%20where%20annual%20temperatures%20will%20reach%20that%20level%20or%20higher%2C%20risking%20danger%20from%20climate%20feedback%20loops%20and%20tipping%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20crossed%2C%20these%20tipping%20points%20could%20change%20our%20climate%20in%20ways%20that%20may%20be%20difficult%20or%20impossible%20to%20reverse%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20could%20include%20the%20meltdown%20of%20the%20ice%20sheets%20in%20Greenland%20and%20West%20Antarctica%2C%20thawing%20of%20large%20areas%20of%20permafrost%20and%20widespread%20coral%20reef%20die%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20some%20tipping%20points%20%26quot%3Bwe're%20not%20going%20to%20avoid%20them%20now%2C%20it's%20more%20about%20slowing%20the%20damage%26quot%3B%2C%20said%20co-author%20Tim%20Lenton%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Global%20Systems%20Institute%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Exeter%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20do%20that%2C%20emissions%20must%20be%20slashed%20and%20temperature%20rise%20curbed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEvery%20fraction%20of%20a%20degree%20matters%2C%20Lenton%20told%20AFP%3A%20%26quot%3BThere's%20still%20a%20lot%20to%20play%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20includes%20the%20number%20of%20people%20who%20might%20face%20intolerable%20conditions%20in%20coming%20decades%2C%20like%20severe%20heat%2C%20limited%20food%20availability%20and%20climate%20extremes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20three%20to%20six%20billion%20people%20could%20be%20%26quot%3Bconfined%20beyond%20the%20livable%20region%26quot%3B%20by%20century's%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20world%20leaders%20have%20generally%20continued%20to%20support%20business%20as%20usual%2C%20rather%20than%20enacting%20policies%20to%20curb%20climate%20change%20and%20sustain%20life%20on%20Earth%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ripple.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20hope%20recent%20extreme%20weather%20events%20will%20help%20motivate%20policymakers%20at%20the%20upcoming%20COP28%20climate%20conference%20to%20support%20massive%20cuts%20in%20fossil%20fuel%20emissions%20and%20increased%20funding%