lium-hydrogen-weather-balloons.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eother%20industries%20are%20increasingly%20using%20hydrogen%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20Space%20Perspective's%20website%2C%20if%20the%20balloon%20happens%20to%20be%20damaged%2C%20it%20will%20descend%20slowly%20to%20the%20ground.%20There%20is%20also%20a%20backup%20parachute%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20prototype%20capsule%20weighs%20over%2014%2C000%20pounds%2C%20and%20the%20Spaceship%20Neptune%20will%20be%20heavier%2C%20Poynter%20said.%20The%20company%20has%20also%20tested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fscientificballoons%2Ftypes-of-balloons%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ezero-pressure%20balloons%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20carry%20much%20heavier%20payloads%20%E2%80%94%20weighing%20over%2022%2C000%20pounds%20%E2%80%94%20than%20the%20Spaceship%20Neptune.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20designed%20the%20Spaceship%20Neptune%20to%20have%20a%20capsule%20that%20was%20well%20within%20the%20normal%20range%20of%20what%20these%20balloons%20carry%2C%26quot%3B%20Poynter%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20first%20commercial%20flights%20are%20planned%20for%202024.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20white%2C%20spherical%20cabin%20above%20the%20earth%20in%20space%20with%20passengers%20taking%20photos%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652b4c1e8bed706e837cc3e9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222813%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20illustration%20of%20the%20Spaceship%20Neptune%20cabin%20in%20space%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Space%20Perspective%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPoynter%20told%20Insider%20that%20only%20unmanned%20tests%20with%20a%20lighter%20prototype%20have%20been%20launched%20so%20far%2C%20mainly%20to%20test%20the%20accuracy%20of%20the%20flight%20trajectory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20actual%20capsule%2C%20which%20is%20capable%20of%20carrying%209%20people%2C%20is%20nea