mmer%20workshop%20for%20kids%20through%20meticulous%20planning%2C%20networking%20and%20creativity%20is%20no%20less%20than%20a%20learning%20opportunity%20for%20any%20business%20school%20student.%20Her%20positive%20attitude%20and%20demeanour%20is%20infectious%20and%20you%20cannot%20say%20no%20to%20a%20request%20from%20Sudha%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%C2%A0A%20Kala%2C%20managing%20committee%20member%2C%20Multiple%20Sclerosis%20Society%20of%20India%20(MSSI)%20of%20the%20Karnataka%20Chapter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20though%20the%20camps%20have%20been%20discontinued%2C%20the%20students%20and%20teachers%20do%20not%20miss%20an%20opportunity%20to%20drop%20in%20and%20spend%20time%20with%20their%20mentor.%20Around%20100%20teachers%20volunteered%20at%20the%20summer%20camp%20over%20the%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20960px)%20100vw%2C%20960px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FIMG-20230928-WA0010_11zon-1698072771.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Located%20at%20the%20Sudha's%20home%20in%20Malleswaram%2C%20which%20was%20thrown%20open%20to%20the%20children%2C%20the%20summer%20camp%20was%20a%20big%20hit.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FIMG-20230928-WA0010_11zon-1698072771.jpg%20960w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FIMG-20230928-WA0010_11zon-1698072771-225x300.jpg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FIMG-20230928-WA0010_11zon-1698072771-500x667.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FIMG-20230928-WA0010_11zon-1698072771-768x1024.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FIMG-20230928-WA0010_11zon-1698072771-640x853.jpg%20640w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FIMG-20230928-WA0010_11zon-1698072771-150x200.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332877%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ELocated%20at%20the%20Sudha%E2%80%99s%20home%20in%20Malleswaram%2C%20which%20was%20thrown%20open%20to%20the%20children%2C%20the%20summer%20camp%20was%20a%20big%20hit.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20days%20at%20the%20summer%20camp%20looked%20like%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20day%20at%20the%20camp%20would%20see%20around%2030%20students%2C%20aged%20between%204%20and%2012%2C%20with%20teachers%20and%20volunteers.%20The%20sessions%20would%20change%20every%20half%20an%20hour%2C%20and%20would%20cover%20music%2C%20art%2C%20drama%2C%20story-telling%20and%20so%20on.%20Sometimes%20experts%20in%20various%20fields%20would%20give%20a%20talk%20on%20their%20subjects%20or%20coach%20the%20children%20in%20the%20art%20of%20miming%2C%20music%20among%20other%20things.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESudha%20herself%20would%20write%20plays%2C%20often%20based%20on%20mythology%2C%20and%20direct%20the%20children%20in%20them.%20Recalling%20one%20such%20play%2C%20Jayshree%2C%20who%20was%20among%20the%20first%20teachers%20to%20join%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20story%20revolved%20around%20the%20River%20Cauvery%20from%20its%20birth%20in%20Coorg%20to%20joining%20the%20sea.%20The%20play%20would%20weave%20in%20the%20cultures%20and%20description%20of%20the%20places%20en%20route.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBy%20noon%20when%20it%20was%20time%20to%20leave%2C%20the%20participants%20would%20be%20treated%20to%20a%20special%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Eprasadam%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20prepared%20in%20the%20house.%20Savitri%2C%20who%20has%20been%20Sudha%E2%80%99s%20help%20for%2035%20years%2C%20also%20helped%20in%20the%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESrimathi%2C%20one%20of%20the%20teachers%2C%20recollects%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20remember%20uncle%20(Mr%20Iyengar)%20pitching%20in%20some%20times%20to%20prepare%20some%20special%20food%20like%20Pizza.%20He%20would%20make%20it%20from%20scratch.%20Once%20he%20was%20preparing%20%3Cem%3Ealoo%20bonda%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20I%20was%20helping%20him%20roll%20the%20potatoes.%20I%20remember%20him%20telling%20me%20to%20make%20them%20big%20enough%20so%20that%20the%20kids%20could%20have%20their%20fill.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20initially%20they%20would%20collect%20Rs%2025%20from%20each%20student%2C%20in%20later%20years%20the%20amount%20was%20increased%20to%20Rs%201000.%20This%20was%20used%20for%20materials%20required%20for%20the%20classes.%20%E2%80%9CAnything%20remaining%20after%20the%20camp%20would%20be%20donated%20to%20NGOs%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Mamatha.%20On%20Sundays%2C%20they%20would%20plan%20some%20special%20activity%2C%20like%20going%20on%20an%20excursion%20to%20nearby%20places%20or%20a%20bird-watching%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20camps%20that%20usually%20ran%20for%203-4%20weeks%20were%20based%20on%20a%20theme%20every%20year.%20This%20would%20be%20decided%20mostly%20by%20Sudha%20but%20in%20consultation%20with%20her%20team%20of%20teachers.%20%E2%80%9CInnovative%20ideas%20were%20welcomed%2C%20like%20the%20%3Cem%3EAata%20Oota%3C%2Fem%3E%20Camp%2C%20which%20involved%20making%20food%20without%20cooking.%20Also%2C%20each%20team%20would%20be%20named%20by%20a%20food%20item%20they%20did%20not%20like.%20This%20was%20done%20to%20foster%20a%20change%20of%20attitude%20towards%20the%20food%20item.%20After%20all%2C%20you%20cannot%20not%20like%20your%20team!%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Srimathi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20come%20to%20enrol%20her%20son%20for%20the%20camp%20but%20felt%20drawn%20to%20assist%20a%20child%20with%20disabilities%20in%20the%20camp.%20Observing%20her%20patience%20and%20how%20the%20child%20obeyed%20her%2C%20Sudha%20took%20it%20upon%20herself%20to%20talk%20to%20Srimathi%E2%80%99s%20husband.%20%E2%80%9CShe%20asked%20him%20to%20get%20me%20admitted%20into%20some%20course%20and%20not%20let%20my%20talent%20go%20to%20waste.%20I%20went%20on%