n%20it%20was%20in%20Beed.%20Water%20was%20very%20scarce%2C%20most%20of%20the%20water%20bodies%20in%20the%20region%20were%20silted%20up%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F288219%2Fafter-visiting-drought-prone-villages-23-yo-plants-3-lakh-trees-in-three-years%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebone%20dry%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20tankers%20were%20the%20only%20way%20of%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20started%20working%2C%20each%20%3Cem%3Etehsil%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20there%20are%208%20in%20Jalna%20district%20%E2%80%94%20survived%20on%20250%20tankers%20per%20day.%20Farmers%20were%20barely%20producing%20anything%20since%20there%20was%20no%20water%20for%20farming%3B%20meeting%20the%20basic%20consumption%20needs%20was%20a%20struggle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20when%20the%20team%20arrived%20in%20the%20district%2C%20villagers%20and%20locals%20were%20highly%20sceptical%20on%20whether%20such%20work%20could%20be%20done%20with%20community%20participation%20and%20through%20the%20efforts%20of%20an%20NGO.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20primarily%20seen%20as%20work%20only%20the%20government%20could%20do%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Narayan%20Devkate%2C%2055%2C%20a%20farmer%20in%20Pimparkhed%2C%20who%20tends%20to%20his%2050-acre%20land%20parcel%20with%20his%20two%20brothers.%20Of%20the%20117-odd%20villages%20in%20his%20vicinity%2C%2078%20had%20no%20water%20at%20all%20when%20the%20effort%20began%2C%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPainstakingly%20and%20with%20gentle%20but%20persistent%20persuasion%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F280255%2Ftamil-nadu-village-pond-revival-malarvizhli-akka-inspiring-water-conservation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20work%20began%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20ranged%20from%20desilting%20and%20rejuvenating%20small%20ponds%2C%20recharging%20borewells%2C%20%3Cem%3Enaali%